Conclusion: The Early‑60s mono LP better preserves the analogue warmth, minimal compression, collective live energy, punchy rhythm section, and cohesive album sequencing I prioritize; candidate 2’s glossy, vocal‑forward remastering would likely undermine those core preferences. Therefore I select the Early‑60s mono LP.

